description:
Open for recipe 

This chickpea recipe for vegan tuna is delicious, nutritious and easy to make. All you need is a can of chickpeas, vegan mayonnaise, onion, garlic, celery, and a few other ingredients. Spread it on a sandwich for a quick and satisfying lunch. Use it as a dip with crackers or chips for a nutritious snack. ForTUNAtely, no fish were harmed making this video!

Vegan Tuna
1 can chickpeas, drained and rinsed
5 tbsp vegan mayonnaise
1 tbsp mustard, if desired
4 tbsp dill pickle, diced
4 tbsp onion, finely diced
1 celery stalk, diced
 tsp kelp powder
Sea salt to taste
2 garlic cloves, crushed
 tsp paprika
Green onions, chopped

Gluten free, nut free, dairy free.
